       <HR>
       <FONT size="+1">Compounds with super<B><I>-aspirin</I></B> effects
</FONT><BR>
       <BR><CENTER><b>Abstract</b></CENTER>
       <p> A compound having the structural formula (I) and pharmaceutically
     acceptable salt and/or hydrates thereof, (I) wherein Y is an arylester or
     an C.sub.1-C.sub.8 alkylaryl ester, selected from the group consisting
     of: benzene, toluene, xylene, benzoic acid, benzoate, nicotinate,
     isonicotinate and halobenzene, which can be unsubstituted or substituted
     with at least one nitric oxide releasing group; and/or at least one of
     hydroxide, --Cl, --Br, a C.sub.1-C.sub.8 alkyl, benzyl, a C.sub.1-C.sub.8
     alkoxy, benzyloxy, --NHC(O)R, --NH.sub.2, --NO.sub.2, --ONO.sub.2,
     --(CH.sub.2).sub.nONO.sub.2, --OC(O)[(CH.sub.2)m], cyclic ONO.sub.2,
     --OCOArONO.sub.2, --OCOAr(CH.sub.2).sub.nONO.sub.2 or a C.sub.1-C.sub.5
     haloalkyl ester, wherein R is a C.sub.1-C.sub.8 alkyl or a
     C.sub.1-C.sub.8 alkoxy group, n=1-8 and m=3-10, to produce a
     super<B><I>-aspirin</I></B> effect.
</p>
       <HR>
