with 33.7% of its deacetylated esterase mediated hydrolysis product isosorbide-2-salicylate-5-nicotinate (23.03 min), along with smaller amounts of aspirin (18.05 min).  Aspirin is deacylated as a result of its mechanism of COX-1 inhibition to salicylic
acid (18.71 min).  Isosorbide-5-nicotinate (14.13 min) was also observed as a byproduct of ST0702 hydrolysis.
